description: I take all my lessons online via zoom meetings. My lessons focus on teaching a way of thinking aimed at solving problems. I do so by integrating basic mathematical principles with fundamental coding approaches before moving on to more advanced concepts. My lessons are highly suitable for students who want to start learning programming from scratch and also for those who need help with understanding specific difficult concepts.

I am a full-stack Software Engineer with a Master's degree from UNSW specialized in Data Science and E-Commerce. I have 2 years of experience in tutoring, more than 4 years of work experience as a software developer. I have expertise in Html/CSS/Javascript, Java, C#, Python, NodeJS, ReactJS, SQL, MongoDB databases, Rest API, Web Designing, and many industrial technologies. I have been tutoring students for the past 2 years and I served as a senior and tech lead at my work, guiding the team with programming and working standards. I will provide simple tasks to understand your current level and explain all the concepts with supporting examples and practice. We will have fun programming creative web applications and solving puzzles.

My teaching flavour depends on who I am teaching. I put together a unique course tailored for each student. This can include projects, step by step tutorials, and problem solving activities, all with a focus on a hands on learning. I have been teaching for many years and still work making games in the games industry as a day job as well as tutoring many regular students. I would love to help you make awesome stuff too, so feel free to message me and we can talk about what I can offer you.
